The Cape Town Cycle Tour has been cancelled due to severe winds in the Cape Peninsula.The extreme winds were expected for most of the route and the organisers of the world&#8217;s largest timed race have announced on Twitter that riders should not approach the start.Yesterday riders were warned about severe weather conditions, but it was decided that it was too dangerous to proceed.David Bellairs of the Cape Town Cycle Tour Trust said the step taken was unprecedented.&#8220;Based on consultation with all the emergency services, the Joint Operations Centre of the Cape Town Cycle Tour 2017 regrets to announce that they have had to take the unprecedented step of cancelling this year s 40th Cycle Tour.&#8221;TNA Reporter 